Package com.naio.canreader.canframeclasses

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CanFrame
    CanFrame represents a frame already parsed from a can a frame look like this : "can0 281#42.45.56" "can0" is the interface, "281" is the id of the message in hexadecimal, it contains the type of the message on 4 bits, the sender on 3 bits and the id message on 4 bits after the # there's the data, in hexadecimal.
    GPSCanFrame
    GPSCanFrame display the data of the GPS: the latitude, longitude, UTC time, and the precision of the gps with the PDOP, HDOP and VDOP
    GSMCanFrame
    Display the data of the GSM
    IHMCanFrame
    Display the data of the IHM
    IMUCanFrame
    Display the data of the IMU
    ISMCanFrame  
    MotorCanFrame  
    MotorLeftCanFrame  
    MotorRightCanFrame  
    VerinCanFrame
    Display the data of the verin and of the ODO
